race.comment: GLIDING LIGHTENING (16) resumes for a leading yard and has raced well in stronger Maidens. She went well in both fresh outings and brings a jumpout win from Pakenham. Maps for the run-of-the-race, and she will be naturally improved. IMZADA (11) resumes after two starts in Open 2 company in town. She was tried at Stakes level on debut, so they have an opinion. Her Flemington jumpouts have been good, and she looks set to go. SWOBODA (14) resumes and has won both jumpouts. She appears improved and can feature with average luck in the run. Ditto APACHE SUNRISE (7), who placed distantly at Swan Hill first-up. Her effort fresh at Seymour three back suggests she has the ability, and she'll present fitter again.
